WEBVTT

00:05.138 --> 00:08.174
<i>[spacey music playing]</i>

00:08.241 --> 00:15.148
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:15.215 --> 00:18.485
- Shit. Um...hey, all,

00:18.551 --> 00:21.521
I don't have a bottle opener.
I thought I did.

00:21.588 --> 00:23.556
- Damn.
You got a lighter?

00:23.656 --> 00:26.693
- I-I do somewhere, maybe,
but it's in one of these boxes,

00:26.760 --> 00:27.927
and that's gonna
be a whole thing.

00:28.028 --> 00:29.195
- Yeah. No, it's cool.

00:29.262 --> 00:31.431
Well, this place is nice.

00:31.531 --> 00:33.500
- It just feels
very divorcey in here.

00:33.566 --> 00:35.101
- That's because
I got a divorce.

00:35.201 --> 00:36.503
- No, no, no, no.

00:36.569 --> 00:37.937
It feels like
I got the divorce.

00:38.038 --> 00:39.372
Like, when I walked in,
it got on me,

00:39.439 --> 00:41.608
like it's in me.
- Yogi, no. Come on.

00:41.708 --> 00:44.711
It's gonna be fine, you know?
Clean slate.

00:44.778 --> 00:46.112
You know, to be honest,

00:46.212 --> 00:47.680
Emily didn't have
a great design sense.

00:47.747 --> 00:49.282
She's a nice girl,
but, you know,

00:49.382 --> 00:50.784
there were
so many fucking pillows.

00:50.884 --> 00:53.086
- Okay, let's slow down there,
new money.

00:53.186 --> 00:54.521
I mean, like,
you just leveled up

00:54.587 --> 00:56.022
from having six roommates.

00:56.089 --> 00:57.757
- Bro, I'm just trying
to give you a win.

00:57.857 --> 00:59.592
It would take a lot more
than an emotional affair

00:59.692 --> 01:01.227
to get me
to leave the West Village.

01:01.294 --> 01:02.929
- Oh, God, I'm gonna miss
that location.

01:03.029 --> 01:05.231
- I told him to stay with her.
Nobody listens to Yogi.

01:05.298 --> 01:06.966
- Okay, Well, thanks
for your support, guys, uh...

01:07.067 --> 01:08.435
[cell phone ringing]

01:08.535 --> 01:11.371
Hey, do y'all wanna watch
a movie or something?

01:11.438 --> 01:14.040
[cell phone continues ringing]

01:15.708 --> 01:17.110
- Yo, what's up?

01:17.210 --> 01:19.446
<i>- Hey, bro, you get your</i>
<i>ticket to Michigan yet?</i>

01:19.546 --> 01:21.915
- Uh, mm, you know,

01:21.981 --> 01:23.416
I-I don't think I can go.

01:23.483 --> 01:26.152
<i>- What are you busy with?</i>
- [clicks tongue]

01:27.153 --> 01:28.822
[exhales] Okay.
I don't want to go.

01:28.922 --> 01:32.325
<i>- Are you serious?</i>
<i>It's their 35th anniversary.</i>

01:32.425 --> 01:34.227
- Yeah, and I love them,
but if I go,

01:34.294 --> 01:36.229
it's gonna be nonstop questions
about my divorce,

01:36.296 --> 01:37.831
and I cannot be
in that environment right now.

01:37.931 --> 01:39.899
The judgment, the shame--
I can't--I can't do it.

01:39.966 --> 01:41.401
I'm out. I'm out.

01:41.468 --> 01:44.070
<i>- Marcus, Mom and Dad</i>
<i>got other shit going on.</i>

01:44.137 --> 01:46.005
<i>They ain't worried about you.</i>

01:46.106 --> 01:48.007
<i>Okay,</i>
<i>Mom is worried about you,</i>

01:48.108 --> 01:50.243
<i>but she's always</i>
<i>been that way.</i>

01:50.310 --> 01:52.178
<i>I'm bringing Keiko,</i>
<i>if that helps.</i>

01:52.278 --> 01:54.848
- How does that help me?

01:54.948 --> 01:57.584
<i>- You just better be</i>
<i>in Michigan next month.</i>

01:57.650 --> 01:59.686
<i>They'll never forgive you</i>
<i>if you miss it.</i>

02:00.620 --> 02:02.822
- [whispering]
This place is fucking dark.

02:02.922 --> 02:05.859
- [whispering]
Yeah. As fuck.

02:06.626 --> 02:07.660
- Hey!

02:09.128 --> 02:10.964
- That's my good side?
- Uh-huh.

02:11.030 --> 02:12.832
- Okay,
get one where I'm laughing

02:12.932 --> 02:14.134
and lost in the moment.

02:14.200 --> 02:15.935
[laughing loudly]

02:16.002 --> 02:17.637
- Can you look
at the road, please?

02:17.704 --> 02:20.773
- Can you shut the fuck up
and let me get my shine on?

02:20.840 --> 02:22.709
[phone vibrating]
- Tom Gilbert is calling again.

02:22.809 --> 02:26.045
- His bitch ass can't manage
by his self for one day, baby.

02:26.146 --> 02:27.347
- Okay. I'm gonna reject it.

02:27.447 --> 02:29.516
- No, no, no. I got it.
I got it.

02:29.616 --> 02:30.650
Yes.

02:30.717 --> 02:32.385
Hi again, Tom.

02:32.485 --> 02:34.120
It's an irrevocable trust.

02:34.187 --> 02:36.789
She can't just change
the beneficiary.

02:37.357 --> 02:39.559
Okay. Bye-bye.

02:40.393 --> 02:42.795
Back to the business.
[both giggle]

02:42.862 --> 02:44.164
Hold up. Diagonal.

02:44.230 --> 02:45.832
Make sure you catch
my ear lobe.

02:45.899 --> 02:49.736
- Oh, honey, your skin
is looking a little dry.

02:50.470 --> 02:52.071
- What you trying to say?
I'm ashy?

02:52.172 --> 02:55.241
- No, but did you use
the lotion that I made for you?

02:55.341 --> 02:57.076
- I can't just use
strange lotions, boo.

02:57.177 --> 02:58.978
- Well, you gotta
use something.

02:59.045 --> 03:00.480
[Marcus chuckles]

03:00.547 --> 03:03.082
- Oh, shit.
Destiny Mathis left a comment.

03:03.183 --> 03:04.350
- Who?

03:04.417 --> 03:05.652
- Destiny Mathis
from high school?

03:05.718 --> 03:07.053
I used to tutor her
in geometry.

03:07.153 --> 03:08.688
- Oh, my God. Destiny.

03:08.755 --> 03:10.590
I used to call her Eternity,
remember?

03:10.690 --> 03:12.325
- Yeah, I remember
she didn't like it.

03:12.392 --> 03:14.394
- Well, she should be mad
at her parents, not me.

03:14.494 --> 03:16.162
<i>- ♪ Groove ♪</i>

03:16.229 --> 03:17.897
<i>♪ And an atmosphere ♪</i>

03:17.997 --> 03:20.900
<i>♪ That's sure</i>
<i>to please you ♪</i>

03:21.000 --> 03:24.704
<i>♪ Ooh,</i>
<i>baby ♪</i>

03:24.771 --> 03:26.272
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:26.372 --> 03:29.442
<i>♪ I gotta get you</i>
<i>home with me tonight ♪</i>

03:29.542 --> 03:31.711
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:33.780 --> 03:35.949
- They're here!
[laughing]

03:36.049 --> 03:37.417
Hey!
- [laughs]

03:37.517 --> 03:39.285
[both squealing]

03:39.385 --> 03:41.588
<i>narrator: For the first time</i>
<i>in nearly seven years,</i>

03:41.688 --> 03:43.957
<i>Marcus was going home</i>
<i>without Emily</i>

03:44.057 --> 03:45.558
<i>and he was bracing himself</i>

03:45.625 --> 03:47.694
<i>for the inevitable</i>
<i>"I told you so's."</i>

03:47.760 --> 03:50.463
<i>When his parents</i>
<i>had rejected Emily,</i>

03:50.563 --> 03:52.465
<i>they had rejected him as well.</i>

03:52.565 --> 03:55.969
<i>And as a result, he felt like</i>
<i>an outsider in his own family.</i>

03:56.069 --> 03:57.637
- Oh!

03:57.737 --> 03:59.606
Oh, Benz look good
on you, kid.

03:59.706 --> 04:01.441
- You know how I do.
[laughter]

04:01.541 --> 04:05.144
Well, Mom and Dad,
this is my girlfriend, Keiko.

04:05.245 --> 04:07.247
- Ida has told me
so much about you.

04:07.313 --> 04:09.315
I'm so excited
to finally meet you.

04:09.415 --> 04:10.583
- Keiko, pleasure to meet you.

04:10.650 --> 04:12.118
I'm glad
you could make it down.

04:12.218 --> 04:14.220
- Yes. We've been looking
forward to meeting you.

04:14.287 --> 04:15.722
Ida doesn't bring
too many girls--

04:15.788 --> 04:17.323
- Mom.
- Oh.

04:17.423 --> 04:18.491
- [gasps]

04:18.591 --> 04:20.827
Get over here, my baby.

04:20.927 --> 04:23.730
- Hey, Mom.
- Oh, my goodness.

04:23.796 --> 04:26.332
- Hey! [laughs]
- Hey!

04:27.800 --> 04:29.002
- Good to see you.

04:29.102 --> 04:30.403
So what's going on
with your hair?

04:30.470 --> 04:31.671
Is this one of those
Brooklyn haircuts

04:31.771 --> 04:33.072
where they don't do nothing,

04:33.139 --> 04:34.574
but they still charge you
a hundred dollars?

04:34.641 --> 04:36.509
- It is.
- Well, I like it.

04:36.609 --> 04:37.910
It's natural.
- Thanks, Mom.

04:37.977 --> 04:39.312
Happy anniversary.

04:39.412 --> 04:41.114
- Happy anniversary.
- Happy anniversary.

04:41.180 --> 04:43.483
Speaking of anniversaries,

04:43.583 --> 04:46.019
this is to thank you
for inviting me

04:46.119 --> 04:47.620
to celebrate with you.

04:47.687 --> 04:49.622
- Oh, thank you.
[inhales]

04:49.689 --> 04:52.358
Fancy soap.
- Handcrafted by me.

04:52.458 --> 04:54.027
- That's real cute, babe.
- Kirby.

04:54.127 --> 04:56.496
You and Marcus
get the luggage out, okay?

04:56.596 --> 04:57.697
- Yes.
- Okay.

04:57.797 --> 04:59.766
And you and Keiko
come with me.

05:01.801 --> 05:04.370
- Ida, your Benz unlocked?
- Sorry.

05:04.470 --> 05:05.538
[car chirps]

05:06.472 --> 05:09.709
- Uh...you do know
it's a rental, right?

05:09.809 --> 05:11.277
- Still impressive.

05:12.979 --> 05:14.347
[laughter]

05:14.447 --> 05:17.116
- Keiko, those soaps!
Really, really love them.

05:17.183 --> 05:20.153
You know, you should sell them.
- Thank you.

05:20.219 --> 05:21.954
I mean, it's more of a hobby,

05:22.021 --> 05:24.223
but I've been thinking about
starting an Etsy business.

05:24.324 --> 05:25.992
- That is such a great idea.

05:26.059 --> 05:27.794
- Mm-mm, don't pump her up
like that.

05:27.860 --> 05:29.729
She already have enough
of her homemade stuff

05:29.829 --> 05:31.197
in my apartment already.

05:31.297 --> 05:34.467
Essential oils, twine,
damn candle wax.

05:34.534 --> 05:36.235
- Okay.
- Mm-mm.

05:36.336 --> 05:38.671
- Well, maybe if I sold some of
it, you wouldn't have so much.

05:38.738 --> 05:40.073
- Well, she got a point.

05:40.173 --> 05:42.241
- Well, if you like it,
I love it.

05:42.342 --> 05:44.077
- And you, did you get
everything squared away

05:44.177 --> 05:46.746
with that Emily situation?

05:46.846 --> 05:48.748
- My divorce?

05:48.848 --> 05:51.517
Yeah. I just let her
keep whatever she wanted.

05:51.584 --> 05:53.219
I mean, she bought
most of it anyway.

05:53.319 --> 05:55.555
- Well, I hope you've taken her
off all the accounts.

05:55.655 --> 05:57.090
The credit's
where they get you.

05:57.190 --> 05:59.392
- Kirby, Marcus is an adult.

05:59.492 --> 06:01.094
He knows how to handle
his affairs.

06:01.194 --> 06:03.696
- You wouldn't know it
by looking at that hairline.

06:03.763 --> 06:04.831
- [chuckles]

06:04.897 --> 06:06.733
[cell phone buzzing]

06:07.767 --> 06:11.037
- No, no, no, I wanna help.
- I can't wait for dessert.

06:11.104 --> 06:13.439
[laughter]

06:13.539 --> 06:16.008
[both murmuring
indistinctly]

06:16.075 --> 06:18.611
- You are so lucky,
you know that?

06:18.711 --> 06:22.014
- Happy anniversary to me!

06:23.282 --> 06:26.686
[mellow R&B playing]

06:26.753 --> 06:28.788
[indistinct chatter,
laughter]

06:28.888 --> 06:31.958
♪ ♪

06:32.058 --> 06:36.396
<i>- ♪ I almost blew my mind ♪</i>

06:36.462 --> 06:39.298
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:39.399 --> 06:40.967
<i>♪ Trying to make ♪</i>

06:41.067 --> 06:43.469
<i>♪ You love me...♪</i>

06:44.704 --> 06:48.040
- Hey, I think I'm gonna head
into town for a little bit.

06:48.107 --> 06:50.309
- But you just got home.
- I know.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.945
I just wanted to unwind.

06:53.045 --> 06:55.882
- Okay, honey, go ahead.
Have fun. Be safe.

06:55.948 --> 06:57.483
- Thanks, Mom.

06:57.583 --> 06:59.285
Ida, keys?

06:59.385 --> 07:00.820
- Where you gotta go?

07:00.920 --> 07:02.255
- Just out.

07:02.321 --> 07:05.391
- You meeting up with Destiny.
Desperate ass.

07:05.458 --> 07:06.826
- Destiny who?

07:06.926 --> 07:08.828
- Uh, Destiny Mathis.

07:08.928 --> 07:11.564
She's a friend of mine
from high school.

07:11.631 --> 07:14.600
It's the girl I used to tutor.

07:14.667 --> 07:17.503
- Destiny. Oh, she was
a sweet little thing.

07:17.603 --> 07:19.772
And she had
a cute little figure too.

07:19.839 --> 07:21.507
- Mom.
- What?

07:21.607 --> 07:23.609
Okay.
Give her a hug for me.

07:23.676 --> 07:25.411
- I will.

07:25.478 --> 07:28.181
Keys?
- They're on the stand.

07:28.281 --> 07:30.850
But if you scratch it,
I'ma beat your ass.

07:30.950 --> 07:32.285
- Okay.

07:34.787 --> 07:36.956
<i>narrator: Marcus never felt</i>
<i>more like a New Yorker</i>

07:37.023 --> 07:38.691
<i>than when he was in Michigan.</i>

07:38.791 --> 07:40.359
<i>While his parents</i>
<i>were making him feel</i>

07:40.460 --> 07:42.862
<i>like a shell</i>
<i>of his former self at home,</i>

07:42.962 --> 07:44.697
<i>out in the world,</i>

07:44.797 --> 07:48.134
<i>he embodied all of the swagger</i>
<i>of a superior coastal elite.</i>

07:48.201 --> 07:49.535
- Hey.
- Hey.

07:49.635 --> 07:51.971
- Can I get a Bulleit, rocks?

07:52.038 --> 07:53.873
- Oh, a top-shelf man.

07:53.973 --> 07:56.976
[funky rock music playing]

07:57.043 --> 07:59.545
♪ ♪

07:59.645 --> 08:02.014
- What's up, smart guy?

08:02.114 --> 08:04.684
[both chuckle]

08:04.784 --> 08:06.953
- I can't believe you still
call me "smart guy."

08:07.019 --> 08:09.222
- What? I love that nickname.

08:09.322 --> 08:10.656
♪ He's a smart guy ♪

08:10.723 --> 08:12.725
- Ah!

08:12.825 --> 08:14.393
That theme song
ruined my life.

08:14.494 --> 08:16.462
- Uh-uh; look, you were
a whole year younger than me,

08:16.529 --> 08:17.897
teaching me geometry
and chemistry.

08:17.997 --> 08:19.732
I needed to even
the playing field.

08:19.832 --> 08:22.301
My ass was getting roasted.

08:22.368 --> 08:25.905
- Well, I mean, if it makes you
feel any better,

08:26.005 --> 08:28.574
I always looked forward
to our sessions.

08:28.674 --> 08:30.009
- Oh!

08:30.076 --> 08:31.511
[stiffly]
Well, I always looked forward

08:31.577 --> 08:34.380
to our sessions, too, Marcus.

08:34.480 --> 08:37.250
- All right. All right.
- [laughs]

08:38.150 --> 08:39.685
- I don't remember you
being this cute

08:39.752 --> 08:41.020
in high school though.

08:41.087 --> 08:42.655
- Yeah, you either.

08:42.722 --> 08:44.891
I'm kidding. I'm kidding.
- I know you are,

08:44.991 --> 08:46.993
'cause I was the shit
in high school, okay?

08:47.059 --> 08:49.495
- Yeah. You still dated
some bums though.

08:49.562 --> 08:51.330
- A habit I am
still trying to break.

08:51.397 --> 08:56.269
♪ ♪

08:56.369 --> 08:59.438
So how long are you in town?

08:59.539 --> 09:03.442
[Marcus and Destiny moaning]

09:06.212 --> 09:08.514
[Destiny laughs]

09:08.581 --> 09:12.218
- I was not expecting that.

09:12.285 --> 09:15.454
- I'm glad you messaged me.
I really needed that tonight.

09:15.555 --> 09:17.957
- Oh, me too.

09:18.057 --> 09:19.125
- Okay.

09:19.225 --> 09:21.727
Well, I'll call my Uber.

09:21.794 --> 09:23.362
- You didn't drive?

09:23.429 --> 09:25.631
- No, I got a boot on my car.

09:25.731 --> 09:29.235
Long story.
- Do you want a ride?

09:29.302 --> 09:31.404
- No. It says it's like
a minute away.

09:32.805 --> 09:35.875
So...am I gonna see you again?

09:35.942 --> 09:40.446
- Yeah. I-I'm just hanging
with my folks, but,

09:40.546 --> 09:42.315
yeah, I'll hit you up.

09:43.149 --> 09:44.483
- Better.

09:44.584 --> 09:46.485
[cell phone buzzes]
It's here.

09:46.586 --> 09:47.820
- All right.
- Mm-hmm.

09:47.920 --> 09:49.221
- [small laugh]

09:56.929 --> 09:59.632
<i>narrator: After a brief</i>
<i>sex-induced moment of clarity</i>

09:59.732 --> 10:02.335
<i>with Destiny,</i>
<i>Marcus felt like a fraud.</i>

10:03.102 --> 10:04.637
<i>He had presented himself</i>
<i>to her</i>

10:04.737 --> 10:07.807
<i>as the same studious,</i>
<i>good-humored Marcus,</i>

10:07.907 --> 10:09.308
<i>not the recently divorced</i>

10:09.408 --> 10:11.444
<i>and demoralized hot mess</i>
<i>with no furniture</i>

10:11.510 --> 10:13.079
<i>that he actually was.</i>

10:13.145 --> 10:15.514
<i>Though</i>
<i>he felt extremely guilty,</i>

10:15.615 --> 10:17.283
<i>he would not call her.</i>

10:17.350 --> 10:19.819
<i>His plan was to simply</i>
<i>slink back to Brooklyn</i>

10:19.919 --> 10:22.855
<i>and hope that she wouldn't</i>
<i>one day curse him out.</i>

10:22.955 --> 10:26.192
<i>-...crashing Maria's car.</i>
<i>Let's go to the core drill.</i>

10:26.292 --> 10:27.994
<i>- Pushed out of bounds,</i>
<i>and the Pittsburgh...</i>

10:28.094 --> 10:29.862
- Oh, come on!

10:29.962 --> 10:32.365
<i>- A big game and 24 yards</i>
<i>on that run.</i>

10:32.465 --> 10:34.533
<i>Paul's gotten blocking</i>
<i>from the blue line,</i>

10:34.634 --> 10:36.802
<i>especially from Slater.</i>

10:36.869 --> 10:38.771
- Uncle Jovan.

10:38.838 --> 10:40.206
- What it do, nephew?

10:40.306 --> 10:41.841
Want some juice?

10:43.476 --> 10:45.444
- No. No, I'm good.

10:48.714 --> 10:50.216
Aren't you early?

10:50.316 --> 10:53.152
- Your mother said
it was a all-day event.

10:53.219 --> 10:54.487
I'm here all day.

10:54.553 --> 10:57.023
<i>- And the snap.</i>
<i>Dixon fades back.</i>

10:57.123 --> 10:59.325
- Oh, come on!

10:59.392 --> 11:00.459
[scoffs]

11:01.861 --> 11:04.563
Give me a hug.
- Oh, hey.

11:04.664 --> 11:07.066
All right. All right.
Good to see you.

11:07.166 --> 11:08.901
Good to see you.
- [chuckling]

11:09.001 --> 11:10.369
I heard you split

11:10.469 --> 11:12.872
with that bad
little white girl you was with.

11:12.972 --> 11:15.841
- Yeah. Yeah, we split up.

11:16.475 --> 11:19.979
- My boy Duane got a divorce
couple months back.

11:20.046 --> 11:21.714
Tried to kill himself.

11:23.749 --> 11:25.151
- Thanks, Uncle.

11:25.217 --> 11:27.219
[cell phone buzzing]

11:28.988 --> 11:30.923
<i>-...three touchdowns</i>
<i>and no interceptions.</i>

11:31.023 --> 11:34.360
<i>And Holey's been on fire.</i>
<i>Holey has four interceptions</i>

11:34.427 --> 11:37.763
<i>on the year, guys, and only</i>
<i>been sacked eight times.</i>

11:37.863 --> 11:41.067
<i>- Their outside lineman</i>
<i>is huge</i>

11:41.167 --> 11:42.568
<i>on the Pittsburgh team.</i>

11:42.668 --> 11:44.603
<i>And the center of the field...</i>

11:44.704 --> 11:46.005
<i>[announcer continues</i>
<i>indistinctly]</i>

11:46.072 --> 11:47.940
- [groaning] Mom.

11:49.041 --> 11:51.877
Mom, why did you invite Destiny
to the party this afternoon?

11:51.944 --> 11:53.279
