18:14.760 --> 18:17.629
- Darnell,
what are you doing here?

18:17.729 --> 18:18.931
Oh, shit.

18:18.997 --> 18:20.332
Uh-uh, uh-uh, uh-uh-uh.

18:20.432 --> 18:22.434
- Fuck that.
- No!

18:22.501 --> 18:23.902
- Lord, Jesus.

18:23.969 --> 18:26.004
[cheers and applause]
- Thank you.

18:26.105 --> 18:27.840
[ahem]

18:27.940 --> 18:29.775
Welcome, family and friends.

18:29.842 --> 18:31.310
- Who the fuck
is this motherfucker?

18:31.410 --> 18:32.778
- He is nobody, D.

18:32.845 --> 18:34.847
He's a friend from high school.
He's harmless.

18:34.947 --> 18:37.583
- To put it plainly...

18:37.649 --> 18:39.351
I couldn't be a luckier man.

18:39.451 --> 18:42.421
Donna, who would've thought
that the first time we met

18:42.488 --> 18:44.523
at that musty-ass Detroit disco

18:44.623 --> 18:46.158
that we'd end up married...

18:46.258 --> 18:50.162
both tenured professors
at the same university...

18:50.262 --> 18:53.465
And yes,
she is the smarter one.

18:53.532 --> 18:54.967
[laughter]
- That's right.

18:55.033 --> 18:57.136
- Could you just stop?
- We take a week off,

18:57.202 --> 19:00.005
and now you fucking
with dark-skin Don Lemon.

19:00.105 --> 19:02.174
Get the--
- Stop!

19:03.108 --> 19:04.776
- Get out the fucking car.

19:04.843 --> 19:07.045
- And look at this beautiful
family we have built together.

19:07.146 --> 19:10.215
Ida, I can't even begin
to express what I've learned

19:10.315 --> 19:11.683
from you over the years.

19:11.783 --> 19:13.886
Your courage
and willingness to be authentic

19:13.986 --> 19:16.989
in every situation
has made me a better man.

19:18.190 --> 19:19.658
- Wait a minute. No.

19:19.725 --> 19:21.727
But when you go to Six Flags
with your baby mama

19:21.827 --> 19:23.629
and I'm upset,
then I'm being extra?

19:23.695 --> 19:25.164
- Is that what you want
right now?

19:25.230 --> 19:27.566
You know that's different.
- No, it's not, D.

19:27.666 --> 19:29.968
I said, "Let's take TJ
to Six Flags."

19:30.035 --> 19:31.236
And then you go with her.

19:31.336 --> 19:32.638
- That's his mother.
- What am I?

19:32.704 --> 19:34.339
Some bitch
he see now and then?

19:34.406 --> 19:35.641
- Don't talk like that.
- Uh-uh.

19:35.707 --> 19:39.011
Why can't I be something
to him too?

19:39.077 --> 19:40.579
Why am I not good enough?

19:40.679 --> 19:42.181
- Is that what this is about?

19:42.247 --> 19:44.249
- And to my son Marcus.

19:45.517 --> 19:47.586
Uh, where are you, Marcus?

19:47.686 --> 19:49.054
- Where is he?

19:49.154 --> 19:50.889
- You know that boy
think the world of you.

19:50.989 --> 19:53.258
- Shut the fuck up, Darnell.
- Yo, I'm serious, girl.

19:53.358 --> 19:55.827
Just the other day,
I tried taking the bikes out.

19:55.894 --> 19:57.062
You know
what this boy said to me?

19:57.162 --> 19:58.397
- What'd he say?

19:58.497 --> 20:00.332
- He said, "I ain't biking
without Dez.

20:00.399 --> 20:02.868
I want Dez."

20:02.935 --> 20:05.103
I wasn't trying to be
disrespectful

20:05.204 --> 20:06.538
with that Six Flag shit.

20:06.605 --> 20:09.575
All this boy do is watch me
and Bianka fight.

20:09.675 --> 20:12.277
I just wanted to have
some moments to look back on

20:12.377 --> 20:13.779
when we felt like a family.

20:13.879 --> 20:15.781
I'm sorry.
I shoulda talked to you first.

20:15.881 --> 20:18.550
- No. No. Maybe...
[quietly] I overreacted.

20:18.617 --> 20:20.352
<i>- ♪ This day ♪</i>

20:20.419 --> 20:22.721
<i>♪ This day ♪</i>
- Missed you, sweetie.

20:22.788 --> 20:24.923
- I missed you too, boo.
- You missed me?

20:25.023 --> 20:27.192
- Yeah.
I love you.

20:27.259 --> 20:29.962
<i>- ♪ This day ♪</i>

20:30.062 --> 20:32.197
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

20:32.264 --> 20:36.568
<i>♪ Yeah...♪</i>

20:36.635 --> 20:43.742
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:01.393 --> 21:02.995
- [exhales]

21:09.434 --> 21:11.069
- Where did you disappear to?

21:11.136 --> 21:13.672
