like it didn't even count.

21:41.033 --> 21:43.769
- No, that is not true.
- Mom, you literally said,

21:43.835 --> 21:46.538
"Do not cut off
all your options just yet"

21:46.638 --> 21:48.774
the second I proposed.

21:48.840 --> 21:51.943
- I just never thought
she was right for you.

21:52.010 --> 21:53.378
- I know you didn't,

21:53.478 --> 21:56.682
but what does it matter
what you think?

21:56.782 --> 21:58.850
It's my life.

22:00.218 --> 22:02.454
You're pushing me
to just get over it all.

22:02.521 --> 22:04.990
"Ah, you're a free man.
You deserve a fresh start."

22:05.057 --> 22:08.060
- You do.
- She is not disposable.

22:08.160 --> 22:10.462
She was my wife.

22:10.529 --> 22:13.532
And it ended because
of something I did.

22:14.132 --> 22:16.968
- I didn't know that.
- Now you know.

22:17.736 --> 22:18.737
Maybe you're right.

22:18.837 --> 22:20.205
Maybe, um...

22:20.305 --> 22:23.175
I just wanted
everyone to back off

22:23.241 --> 22:26.578
so I could do my own thing.

22:28.046 --> 22:31.483
But, Mom, I hurt her
and I hurt myself

22:31.550 --> 22:34.152
